Sentencas: Using a D-optimal design of experiments, the influences of feedstock powder and plasma gases on deposition efficiency, gas tightness, and the electrochemical behavior of vacuum plasma-sprayed yttria-stabilized zirconia for solid oxide fuel cell electrolytes were examined.
Titulo: Improving plasma-sprayed yttria-stabilized zirconia coatings for solid oxide fuel cell electrolytes

Sentencas: In-flight particle temperature and velocity, measured by online particle diagnostics, were correlated with plasma and deposit properties.
Titulo: Improving plasma-sprayed yttria-stabilized zirconia coatings for solid oxide fuel cell electrolytes

Sentencas: Electrochemical testing of cells was performed to determine the influence of gas tightness and microstructure of electrolyte deposit on cell behavior.
Titulo: Improving plasma-sprayed yttria-stabilized zirconia coatings for solid oxide fuel cell electrolytes
